## Step 3 — Start Debugging

Press **F5** in VS Code — it will launch Chrome connected to your debugger.

Now you can:
- Set **breakpoints** by clicking left of any line number in your JS files
- See **variables** in the left debug panel
- Use the **Debug Console** at the bottom to run JS commands live

---

## Step 4 — Set Breakpoints in auth.js

Since you want to debug the login and user management, open `js/auth.js` and click to set breakpoints on these key lines:
```
Line: const hash = await _hash(password);     ← see the password hash
Line: const users = await _af('/rest/v1/...')  ← see Supabase response
Line: return { ok: true, session }             ← confirm login success
```

---

## Step 5 — Open login.html Directly

In the browser that opens, navigate to:
```
http://localhost:5500/login.html